{"article_id":"NbUJwdVtRNVbtN5S","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"BERKELEY -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"UC Berkeley has been long heralded as the birthplace of the country ' s free speech movement .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"after violent protests this week forced the school to cancel the scheduled appearance of alt-right icon Milo Yiannopoulos ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"some are wondering","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"if Berkeley is where free speech is hitting a roadblock .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"After the protest on Wednesday evening by more than 1,500 demonstrators outside the Martin Luther King Jr. Student Union began to turn violent ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"instigated in part by what campus officials described as outsiders ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"the event was called off .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"On Thursday , the Berkeley College Republicans ,","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"who had hosted Yannopoulos ' appearance ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"summed up their disappointment this way :","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"\" The Free Speech Movement is dead , \"","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"the group said in a statement","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"posted on its website .","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"\" Last night , the Berkeley College Republicans ' constitutional right to free speech was silenced by criminals and thugs","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"seeking to cancel Milo Yiannopoulos ' tour .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"Their success is a defeat for civilized society and the free exchange of ideas on college campuses across America . \"","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"The group thanked the campus police and university administration","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"\" for doing all","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"they could","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"to ensure the safety of everyone involved .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"It is tragic that the birthplace of the Free Speech Movement is also its final resting place . \"","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"While the rest of the world may see student protesters as the ones behind the violence ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"campus officials on Thursday said","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"non-students had hijacked what otherwise would have been a peaceful protest .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"And they referred pointedly to the fact","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that the Berkeley campus has been and will remain a bastion of protected speech ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"no matter what part of the ideological landscape its practitioners may inhabit .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"\" We are proud of our history and legacy as the home of the Free Speech Movement , \"","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"UC spokesman Dan Mogulof said Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"\" While we have made clear our belief","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"that the inflaming rhetoric and provocations of Mr. Yiannopoulos were in marked opposition to the basic values of the university ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"we respected his right","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"to come to campus","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"and speak","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"once he was invited to do so by a legitimate student group . \"","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"Mogulof said","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"the violent protesters had waged an assault not simply on the physical campus , but on the free-speech ideals","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"enshrined at UC Berkeley ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"\" which stands for and helps to maintain and nurture open inquiry and an inclusive civil society , the bedrock of a genuinely democratic nation .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"We are now ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"and will remain in the future ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"completely committed to Free Speech as essential to our educational mission and a vital component of our identity at UC Berkeley . \"","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Berkeley Mayor Jesse Arreguin , a Cal graduate , also weighed in ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"saying in a statement","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that the free-speech traditions don ' t stop at the campus border ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and he blasted the violent protesters for their actions .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"\" I represent a city","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that stands united for community , for inclusion , and for a peaceful dialogue about the issues ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"and that stands united against bigotry , united against fear mongering , and united against violence towards anyone , \"","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"said the mayor .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"\" For our community to be a beacon of light in these dark times ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"we must display our values of inclusion ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"keep each other and our community safe ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"embrace our right","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"to peacefully assemble ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"and show the rest of the country our values in both speech and in action . \"","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"Some","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"who were on hand for the protest","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"were conflicted","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"- upset","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that the university ' s actions were a black eye for free speech ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"but recognizing","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"that the level of violence","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"erupting outside the venue","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"dictated at the last minute","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"that the event be stopped .","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"\" The Free Speech Movement started here","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"and now we can ' t let certain people speak ? ' '","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"said UC Berkeley student Danny Phan .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"\" That ' s kind of hypocritical .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"In a way , I see the school ' s decision as going against free speech ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"but I also think","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"they were justified","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"in cancelling the speech","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"because I was there","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"and saw","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"the people","depth":17},{"id":79,"text":"wearing masks","depth":18},{"id":80,"text":"burning things","depth":19},{"id":81,"text":"and smashing windows .","depth":19},{"id":82,"text":"If they ' d let the speech go on ,","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"it would have gotten a lot worse . ' '","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"Phan wondered","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"whether the school ' s real mistake was not in shutting the event down","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"but in not being properly prepared for trouble .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"\" While free speech has taken a hit here ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"I don ' t think","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"it ' s dead , \"","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"said the political-science major .","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"\" The next time , though , the school should be better prepared .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"It was these third-party actors , not us students , who sabotaged everything . ' '","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"The university knew for weeks","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"that Yiannopoulos ' appearance could prompt violent protests","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"that could in turn threaten the school ' s long tradition","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"of facilitating free speech at every turn .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"In a statement last week , Chancellor Nicholas Dirks wrote","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"that \" the concerns around the upcoming visit of a controversial speaker to campus make it necessary for us to reaffirm our collective commitment \" to free expression ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"calling the university \" a site of open inquiry and learning . \"","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Referring to Berkeley ' s commitment to free speech ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"he said","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"the school has \" gone so far as to defend in court the constitutional rights of students of all political persuasions","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"to engage in unpopular expression on campus . \"","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"And that expression ,","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"he wrote ,","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"would include Yiannopoulos ,","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"whom Dirks called \" a troll and provocateur","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"who uses odious behavior in part","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"to ' entertain , '","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"but also to deflect any serious engagement with ideas .","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"He has been widely and rightly condemned for engaging in hate speech . \"","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"Dirk said last week","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"that the school was working closely with police","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"to prepare ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"to \" ensure","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"the event goes","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"as planned ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"and to provide for the safety and security of those","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"who attend ,","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"as well as those","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"who will choose to protest Yiannopoulos ' s appearance in a lawful manner . \"","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"On Thursday , school officials did not respond to questions about those preparations","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"and whether officials had failed to properly protect free speech on campus","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"by having enough police officers on hand","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"to prevent violence from interfering with the speech .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"In a statement , campus police officials said","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"the appearance by Yiannopoulos was cancelled \" amid violence , destruction of property , and out of concern for public safety . \"","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"\" Of paramount importance this evening was the campus ' s commitment","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"to ensure the safety and security of those","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"attending the event , the speaker , those","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"who came to engage in lawful protest ,","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"as well as members of the public and the Berkeley campus community , \"","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"the police said .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"The release described \" fires","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"that were deliberately set ,","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"one outside the campus Amazon outlet ;","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Molotov cocktails","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"that caused generator-powered spotlights to catch fire ;","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"commercial-grade fireworks","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"thrown at police officers ;","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"barricades","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"pushed into windows","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"and skirmishes within the crowd were among the evening ' s violent acts . \"","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"Alan Schlosser , Senior Counsel with the ACLU of Northern California , said","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"without knowing precisely what sort of public-safety threats prompted Cal police to act","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"it was difficult to assess their decision .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"But he said","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"\" the university has a clear obligation to provide controversial speakers the right","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"to speak","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"and not to cave in to threats or disruptions , say , by hecklers .","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"\" In this case , ' '","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"\" the university knew beforehand about the threats","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"and did not give in to them","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"by cancelling the speech in advance .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"And it does seem that the actions last night went beyond simply being threats of disruption .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"If people there opposed to the speaker","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"created a truly dangerous situation ,","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"then the university was within its rights","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"to cancel the speech .","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"\" No speaker has an absolute right","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"to speak ' '","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"if the protests","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"triggered \" cause an imminent danger to people , \"","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"said Schlosser .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"\" I just don ' t know","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"if things last night reached that point . ' '","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"Staff writers Rick Hurd and Katy Murphy also contributed to this story .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":339,"left":0,"right":338,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":338,"left":337,"right":169,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":337,"left":261,"right":336,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":177,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":174,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":1,"right":173,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":173,"left":171,"right":172,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":175,"right":8,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":211,"right":259,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":211,"left":204,"right":210,"relation":